# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# bas-celik — a program for reading smart-card documents issued by the
#             government of Serbia (Go, 341★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/ubavic/bas-celik
# author : Виктор Убавић (Viktor Ubavić, ubavic)
# license: MIT
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from internal/
# flags.go on the ubavic/bas-celik v2 tip — Go stdlib `flag.Bool` /
# `flag.String` / `flag.Uint` registrations parsed exactly as declared.
#
# Direct deps from go.mod (selected):
#   github.com/signintech/gopdf  v0.36.0  ← canonical Go pure-language
#                                            PDF generation library
#                                            (this axis) — by the
#                                            Signintech collective
#                                            (Thailand-based fintech
#                                            startup that open-sourced
#                                            their internal PDF gen
#                                            library); pure-Go writer
#                                            for PDF 1.7 with embedded
#                                            TTF fonts, CMYK/RGB color
#                                            spaces, gradients, vector
#                                            paths, and Unicode-aware
#                                            text layout.  Succeeded
#                                            jung-kurt/gofpdf (archived
#                                            2022 by upstream) as the
#                                            de-facto Go PDF generator.
#   github.com/ebfe/scard                  (PC/SC smart-card bindings —
#                                            access ISO-7816 contact
#                                            cards through OS PC/SC
#                                            daemon: pcscd on Linux,
#                                            CryptoTokenKit on macOS,
#                                            Resource Manager on
#                                            Windows)
#   fyne.io/fyne/v2                        (cross-platform GUI for the
#                                            default GUI mode when no
#                                            -pdf/-excel/-json/-list/
#                                            -atr/-version flag is set)
#
# bas-celik reads Serbian government-issued smart cards (national ID
# card, RFZO medical insurance card, vehicle registration) over PC/SC,
# extracts the document data, and exports it as PDF (printable copy
# matching the official Serbian government PDF layout), Excel, or JSON.
# Without flags, the program launches a Fyne-based GUI showing the card
# data inline.  PDF export uses `signintech/gopdf` directly to render
# the printable copy with Cyrillic-aware text layout (toggleable via
# `-cyrillic-labels`).  Medical-card export can optionally fetch the
# `validUntil` date from the RFZO public API (`-rfzoValidUntil`).
#
# === AXIS 174 CONTINUES — pure-language PDF generation libraries ========
# Axis position: Go=229 continues Axis 174 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# pure-language PDF generation library is `github.com/signintech/gopdf`
# — pure-Go PDF 1.7 writer with no system C dependencies, embedded TTF
# font subsetting, Unicode-aware text layout (including CJK + Cyrillic),
# vector paths, gradients, RGB/CMYK color spaces.  Succeeded jung-kurt/
# gofpdf (the original Go PDF library, archived 2022 by maintainer
# Kurt Jung; was a port of the PHP fpdf library to Go).  The other
# major alternative is `pdfcpu/pdfcpu` but pdfcpu is focused on PDF
# manipulation (merge/split/encrypt/optimize) rather than generation
# from scratch.  Used by maaslalani/invoice (CLI invoice generator),
# 1Panel-dev/1Panel (server admin panel PDF reports), torabian/fireback
# (Go backend framework), bas-celik (Serbian smart-card reader),
# mikeshimura/goreport, and most modern Go CLIs that need PDF output
# without dragging in libharu/wkhtmltopdf system dependencies.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=229     _paper-age            ← previous round (axis 174 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=229       ← THIS FILE           (axis 174 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=229  ← next round          (axis 174 CLOSES at triple-229, 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_bas-celik() {
    _arguments -s \
        '-atr[print the ATR (Answer To Reset) from the card and exit]' \
        '-cyrillic-labels[print ID PDF with cyrillic labels (ignored for non-ID cards)]' \
        '-excel=[Excel export path]:file:_files -g "*.xlsx"' \
        '-json=[JSON export path]:file:_files -g "*.json"' \
        '-list[list connected smart-card readers and exit]' \
        '-pdf=[PDF export path (rendered via signintech/gopdf in Serbian government layout)]:file:_files -g "*.pdf"' \
        '-rfzoValidUntil[fetch the medical card insurance valid-until date from the RFZO public API (ignored for non-medical cards)]' \
        '-verbose[provide additional details in the terminal]' \
        '-version[display version information and exit]' \
        '-reader=[set the PC/SC reader index (default 0; use -list to see indices)]:reader index:'
}

_bas-celik "$@"
